headline: Should Investors Revisit Southwest After Its Recent 5% Stock Climb?
summary: If you’re watching Southwest Airlines and wondering whether now is the right time to buy in, you’re not alone. The stock has been quietly climbing, up 5.1% over the past week and 5.4% across the last month, which is catching the attention of investors looking for signs of recovery or momentum. Year to date, the stock is practically flat, and while the one-year return sits at 13.2%, the five-year path has been bumpy, down 15.0% from where it was. This recent uptick is partly driven by a...
